BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:EVOME Institute Science Journalism Fellowship
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T000000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T000000
UID:3560a3dadc7dba505f62c5349d4ec2e3@sej.org
DESCRIPTION:The Woodwell Climate Research Center's EVOME Institute is now 
 accepting applications for science journalism fellows. The National Scien
 ce Foundation-supported Evolving Meta-Ecosystems Institute (EVOME) will pr
 ovide fellowships for six science journalists to participate in a two-week
  immersion in interdisciplinary evolutionary and global change biology bei
 ng conducted at the University of Alaska’s Toolik Field Station in north
 ern Alaska. Fellowships will cover transportation costs to and from the To
 olik Field Station through Fairbanks\, AK\, plus room and board. Deadline:
  Mar. 27\, 2026.\n\nCategories: National (U.S.)\, Workshops and Fellowship
 s\, Biodiversity\, Climate Change\, Environmental Studies\, Other or All\,
  Science
URL:https://www.sej.org/calendar/deadline-evome-institute-science-journali
 sm-fellowship
X-SOURCE:Society of Environmental Journalists
END:VEVENT
